## Session protocol
- Commit after each logical change (max 3-5 files per commit)
- git checkpoint before any multi-file refactor
- Clear commit messages: "feat/fix/chore(scope): what — why"
- At session end: npm test + npm run validate + npm run build — all green
- Update PLAN.md "Recently Completed" section
- Update REVAMP_PLAN.md with new session section
- Open PR with summary

## Quality standards
- No placeholder comments (// TODO) — complete or skip
- No "Loading..." text — use .skeleton CSS shimmer
- Every animation: prefers-reduced-motion media query
- Every interactive element: min 44px touch target
- Every price: font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums + freshness label
- Every button/link/card: hover + focus-visible states
- Every internal link: must resolve to a real file

## Known issues to always check for
- Product name must be "Gold Ticker Live" (not "Gold Tracker Pro", not "GoldPrices")
- Data source must say gold-api.com (not goldpricez.com)
- Karat set must come from src/config/karats.js (don't hardcode different sets per page)
- node_modules/ and dist/ must NOT be in git
